97620702.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hjz1705997620702.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hjz1705997620702.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hjz1705997620702\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A predefined value for the properties of UX widgets, which is an instance of empty\n\t\tobject, and is shown as an empty object {} in JavaScript debugger.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.RESET</code></p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hjz1705997620702__section_n2t_42s_21c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572791e53\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">It is used as a constant value. It is read-only value and cannot be changed.</p>\n<div class=\"p\">It can be compared by strict equality (triple equals) \"===\", for\n\t\t\t\texample:<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104hjz1705997620702_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"hjz1705997620702__codeblock_o3y_hfs_21c\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">if (value === uniface.RESET) { \n    //... \n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">It appears as a property value in the data argument of <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate</code> API method\n\t\t\t\tof UX widgets. For more details, see <cite class=\"cite\">Predefined property value:\n\t\t\t\t\tuniface.RESET</cite> section in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tpd1701568145998.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tpd1701568145998.html\" title=\"Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed.\">dataUpdate</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tpd1701568145998.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>dataUpdate</a><p>Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udc1665702532677.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uniface</a><p>The uniface object enables you to obtain information about DSP instances.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828553\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828553\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "RESET Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 25, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A predefined value for the properties of UX widgets, which is an instance of empty object, and is shown as an empty object {} in JavaScript debugger. uniface.RESET Description It is used as a constant value. It is read-only value and cannot be changed. It can be compared by strict equality (triple equals) \"===\", for example: Explain this code if (value === uniface.RESET) { //... } Copy It appears as a property value in the data argument of dataUpdate API method of UX widgets. For more details, see Predefined property value: uniface.RESET section in dataUpdate . Related Links dataUpdate Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed. uniface The uniface object enables you to obtain information about DSP instances. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}